1 All trees

1.1 Frequency and probability table: GENSUSPECI vs STREETTREE

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data = top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        "all")
    t = table(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI, chicago_tree_data$STREETTREE)
    t = cbind(t, round(t[, 1]/length(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI), 
        3), round(t[, 2]/length(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI), 
        3), round(t[, 3]/length(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI), 
        3))
    colnames(t) <- c("#_blank", "#_!street", "#_street", "prob_blank", 
        "prob_!street", "prob_street")
    return(t[order(-t[, "prob_street"]), ])
}

2 Top 10 species

2.1 Probability bar chart: GENSUSPECI vs STREETREE

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data = top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    barplot_table <- table(subset(chicago_tree_data, select = c(GENUSSPECI, 
        STREETTREE)))
    barplot(prop.table(barplot_table), legend.text = rownames(barplot_table), 
        beside = TRUE, names.arg = c("Unkown", "Not street tree", 
            "Street tree"), col = rainbow(nrow(barplot_table)), 
        args.legend = list(x = "topleft", bty = "n"))
}

2.2 Species probability table for each land use category

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data <- top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    t <- table(chicago_tree_data$LU, chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI)
    p <- round(t/rowSums(t), 3)
    rownames(p) <- landUse[as.numeric(rownames(p)) + 1, 2]
    return(p)
}

2.3 Species probability pie chart for each land use category

function () 
{
    p <- as.data.frame(t(run_4()))
    colnames(p) = c("GENUSSPECI", "LU", "Probabilty")
    num_spp = length(unique(p$GENUSSPECI))
    p <- ggplot(p, aes(x = "", fill = GENUSSPECI, y = Probabilty)) + 
        geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity") + facet_wrap(~LU) + 
        coord_polar("y") + xlab("") + ylab("") + scale_fill_manual("Species", 
        values = rainbow(num_spp)) + theme(axis.text.x = element_blank())
    return(p)
}

2.4 Species probability horizontal bar for each land use category

function () 
{
    p <- as.data.frame(t(run_4()))
    colnames(p) = c("GENUSSPECI", "LU", "Probabilty")
    num_spp = length(unique(p$GENUSSPECI))
    p <- ggplot(p, aes(x = LU, fill = GENUSSPECI, y = Probabilty)) + 
        geom_bar(width = 0.9, stat = "identity") + xlab("") + 
        ylab("") + scale_fill_manual("Species", values = rainbow(num_spp)) + 
        coord_flip()
    return(p)
}

2.5 Box plot: GENUSSPECI vs HEIGHT_MAX (with N values)

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data <- subset(chicago_tree_data, HEIGHT_MAX > 
        0)
    chicago_tree_data <- top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    num_spp = length(unique(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI))
    p <- ggplot(chicago_tree_data, aes(x = GENUSSPECI, y = HEIGHT_MAX)) + 
        geom_boxplot(fill = rainbow(num_spp)) + scale_x_discrete(name = "Species") + 
        scale_y_continuous(name = "Height (feet)") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, 
        hjust = 1)) + stat_summary(fun.data = function(x) {
        c(y = -3, label = length(x))
    }, geom = "text")
    return(p)
}

2.6 Box plot: GENUSSPECI vs HEIGHT_MAX with LU facet

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data <- subset(chicago_tree_data, HEIGHT_MAX > 
        0)
    chicago_tree_data <- top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    chicago_tree_data <- cbind(chicago_tree_data, LU_DESC = landUse$description[match(unlist(chicago_tree_data$LU + 
        1), landUse$LU)])
    p <- ggplot(chicago_tree_data, aes(x = GENUSSPECI, y = HEIGHT_MAX)) + 
        geom_boxplot(aes(fill = GENUSSPECI)) + scale_x_discrete(name = "Species") + 
        scale_y_continuous(name = "Height (feet)") + theme(axis.text.x = element_blank()) + 
        facet_wrap(~LU_DESC)
    return(p)
}

2.7 Scatter plot: HEIGHT_MAX vs DBH_IN with GENUSSPECI facet

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data <- top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    chicago_tree_data <- subset(chicago_tree_data, HEIGHT_MAX > 
        0 & DBH_IN > 0 & HEIGHT_MAX/DBH_IN <= 30)
    p <- ggplot(chicago_tree_data, aes(x = DBH_IN, y = HEIGHT_MAX, 
        colour = HEIGHT_MAX/DBH_IN)) + geom_point(alpha = 1/25) + 
        scale_y_continuous(name = "Height (feet)") + scale_x_continuous(name = "DBH (inches)", 
        limits = c(0, 60)) + facet_wrap(~GENUSSPECI) + scale_colour_gradientn(colours = rainbow(30))
    return(p)
}
Warning: Removed 13 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

3 Genus-specific

3.1 Box plot: GENUSSPECI vs HEIGHT_MAX within Quercus genus (with N values)

function () 
{
    chicago_tree_data <- chicago_tree_data[grepl("Quercus*", 
        chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI), ]
    chicago_tree_data <- subset(chicago_tree_data, HEIGHT_MAX > 
        0)
    chicago_tree_data <- top_spp(chicago_tree_data, "GENUSSPECI", 
        10)
    num_spp = length(unique(chicago_tree_data$GENUSSPECI))
    p <- ggplot(chicago_tree_data, aes(x = GENUSSPECI, y = HEIGHT_MAX)) + 
        geom_boxplot(fill = rainbow(num_spp)) + scale_x_discrete(name = "Species") + 
        scale_y_continuous(name = "Height (feet)") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, 
        hjust = 1)) + stat_summary(fun.data = function(x) {
        c(y = -3, label = length(x))
    }, geom = "text")
    return(p)
}
